description:
&lt;p&gt;There are lots of good reasons to come and work at Surrey &amp; Sussex NHS Healthcare Trust; recently inspected by the CQC and rated as Outstanding being just one of them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the growth and development of our service a newly created post is now available providing an exciting opportunity for a full-time diabetes specialist nurse to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The diabetes multidisciplinary specialist team are based in a dedicated diabetes centre, The Earlswood Community Diabetes &amp; Endocrinology Centre, within the beautiful grounds of the Royal Earlswood Estate. This is a ten minute walk to East Surrey Hospital enabling effective links to the acute services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone dynamic, with excellent communication skills, time management and leadership skills, who can demonstrate that they are passionate about working collaboratively with people with diabetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As an autonomous practitioner you will be responsible for managing your own caseload of complex patients. You will work closely with all members of the wider multidisciplinary diabetes care team and therefore should demonstrate high quality interpersonal skills.&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will have personal qualities appropriate to this high profile role and will be fully supported in developing their professional expertise as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 20th November 2020 although this may need to be change&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Susan Stockley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Consultant Diabetes &amp; Genetic Specialist Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: susan.stockley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01737 231 788&lt;/p&gt;
